    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-slow-cooked-beef-brisket-and-red-wine-cottage-pie-with-broccoli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and <strong>carrot</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softening</p><p>Tip: Add a small splash of cold water if it starts to burn!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-slow-cooked-beef-brisket-and-red-wine-cottage-pie-with-broccoli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, transfer your <strong>slow cooked beef brisket </strong>to a clean board<strong> </strong>(reserve the juices!)<strong> </strong>and shred it apart, using 2 forks \u2013 this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-slow-cooked-beef-brisket-and-red-wine-cottage-pie-with-broccoli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant, then add the <strong>shredded beef</strong> with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until well coated</p><p>Add your <strong>red wine paste</strong>, <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>beef juices</strong> and 250ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil then transfer to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Tip: Use individual dishes for fancy presentation!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-slow-cooked-beef-brisket-and-red-wine-cottage-pie-with-broccoli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the dish[es] in the oven, uncovered, for 15-20 min or until tender and the sauce has thickened, then remove from the oven and turn the grill to high</p><p>Whilst the beef is cooking, peel your<strong> potatoes</strong> and chop them into bite-sized pieces, then add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender then drain the potatoes and return to the pot to steam dry</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-slow-cooked-beef-brisket-and-red-wine-cottage-pie-with-broccoli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the<strong> potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a generous splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth, then add most of your <strong>crispy onions</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and 1/3 of the <strong>grated cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest for topping!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy onion mash</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-slow-cooked-beef-brisket-and-red-wine-cottage-pie-with-broccoli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>slow cooked beef & red wine</strong> with the <strong>crispy onion mash</strong> (reserve and rinse the pot) and the <strong>remaining grated cheese</strong> then put under the grill for 5-7 min or until lightly browned \u2013 this is your <strong>the</strong> <strong>ultimate slow cooked beef brisket & red wine cottage pie</strong></p><p>Trim, then add your <strong>green beans</strong> to the reserved pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them)</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender then drain, add a knob of <strong>butter </strong>with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-slow-cooked-beef-brisket-and-red-wine-cottage-pie-with-broccoli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve <strong>the</strong> <strong>ultimate slow cooked beef brisket & red wine cottage pie</strong> with the <strong>buttery green beans</strong> to the side</p><p>Top the pie with the<strong> remaining crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
